{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a70417cc3fb48d6844d", "type": "numerical", "level": 2, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 180, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "648b5a3a0d9d0b909f7b648f", "title": "JEE Main 2023 (08 Apr Shift 2)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "Two transparent media having refractive indices <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math> are separated by a spherical refracting surface of radius of curvature <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>. The centre of curvature of surface is towards denser medium and a point object is placed on the principal axis in rarer medium at a distance of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math> from the pole of the surface. The distance of image from the pole of the surface is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cm</mi></math>.", "image": null}, "options": [], "correctValue": "30", "solution": {"text": "<blockquote><p>Let&#39;s consider the following diagram-</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/0474b6b0-a2e6-4a25-88ef-05d2d291e0e1-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 237px;\" /></p><p>The relation between the object distance, the image distance and the radius of curvature&nbsp;of the spherical surface can be written as</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>v</mi></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mi>u</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Substitute the values of the known parameters into equation (1) and solve to calculate the required image distance.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow><mi>v</mi></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mn>30</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8658;</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow><mi>v</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>60</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>15</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8658;</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>30</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>Hence, the image is formed at a distance of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>&nbsp;from the pole on the same direction as the object is placed.</p></blockquote>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ89548594", "numericalLowerLimit": 30, "numericalUpperLimit": 30, "bucket": "Tough Ques (JEE Adv)", "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283d